On the basis of this course the students will learn the:
- translating of Old-Babylonian poetic texts;
- analyzing their grammar, phonology, morphology and syntax;
- dealing with some aspects of a textual critical analysis of appropriate poetic texts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to:
- get an overview of the grammatical and syntactical structure, phonology and morphology of the Babylonian language of the Old Babylonian period (1st half of the 2nd Millennium B.C.); 
- study the basics of translating appropriate poetic texts like the prologue of the Codex Hammurapi.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students will: - know the grammatical structure, phonology and morphology of Old-Babylonian; - understand the phonological and morphological development of Babylonian during the 2nd and 1st Millennium B.C. - be able to analyze all nominal and verbal forms with pre-, in- and suffixes; - know the basic Babylonian vocabulary of some hundreds of words; - be able to use relevant dictionaries and vocabularies; - translate appropriate poetic texts of the Old-Babylonian period with the help of the dictionaries (especially CAD).
